item.description:
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Welcome to my new, under-construction blog. It is built using the following tools:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;ulist&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jbake.org&quot;&gt;JBake&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gradle.org&quot;&gt;Gradle&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jbake-org/jbake-gradle-plugin&quot;&gt;JBake Gradle Plugin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://asciidoctor.org&quot;&gt;AsciiDoctor&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The page templates use &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thymeleaf.org&quot;&gt;Thymeleaf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is published to Github with the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/ajoberstar/gradle-git&quot;&gt;Gradle Github Pages Plugin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I was inspired to use the approach by &lt;a href=&quot;http://melix.github.io/blog/&quot;&gt;Cédric Champeau&lt;/a&gt;, who wrote the JBake Gradle Plugin and a blog post, &lt;a href=&quot;http://melix.github.io/blog/2014/02/hosting-jbake-github.html&quot;&gt;Authoring your blog on GitHub with JBake and Gradle&lt;/a&gt;, about how he created his blog.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m doing a few things differently from Cédric:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;olist arabic&quot;&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;arabic&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My site/blog is a &lt;a href=&quot;https://help.github.com/articles/user-organization-and-project-pages/#user&amp;#8212;&amp;#8203;organization-pages&quot;&gt;GitHub User Page&lt;/a&gt;, his is a &lt;a href=&quot;https://help.github.com/articles/user-organization-and-project-pages/#project-pages&quot;&gt;Github Project Page&lt;/a&gt; (for repository &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/melix/blog&quot;&gt;melix/blog&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;olist loweralpha&quot;&gt;
&lt;ol class=&quot;loweralpha&quot; type=&quot;a&quot;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The repository name is of the format &lt;code&gt;username.github.io&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The source code lives in the &lt;code&gt;source&lt;/code&gt; branch and the rendered HTML is pushed to the &lt;code&gt;master&lt;/code&gt; branch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m using the Thymeleaf &lt;a href=&quot;http://jbake.org/docs/2.4.0/#templates_directory&quot;&gt;JBake templates&lt;/a&gt; (and Cédric is using &lt;a href=&quot;http://freemarker.org&quot;&gt;Freemarker&lt;/a&gt;&amp;#8201;&amp;#8212;&amp;#8201;what, not &lt;a href=&quot;http://melix.github.io/blog/2014/02/markuptemplateengine.html&quot;&gt;Groovy&lt;/a&gt;?)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;#8217;m also hoping to migrate content from &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.msgilligan.com&quot;&gt;www.msgilligan.com&lt;/a&gt;, my 10-year-old &lt;a href=&quot;http://docbook.sourceforge.net/release/website/example/&quot;&gt;DocBook Website&lt;/a&gt;-powered site, register a &lt;a href=&quot;https://help.github.com/articles/setting-up-a-custom-domain-with-github-pages/&quot;&gt;custom domain&lt;/a&gt;, and replace that site. I&amp;#8217;ve used XSLT to convert my DocBook-Website XML files to regular &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.docbook.org&quot;&gt;DocBook XML&lt;/a&gt; and then &lt;a href=&quot;http://pandoc.org&quot;&gt;PanDoc&lt;/a&gt; to convert them to AsciiDoc format. Some manual massaging is still needed. Stay tuned&amp;#8230;&amp;#8203;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
